    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://anchorage.craigslist.org/fbh/6043952992.html"></div>
        </div>
Piper's Restaurant and Sports Lounge at the Coast International Inn is looking for a new Food & Beverage Manager that is motivated, hard-working, and wants to excel at his/her position.  <br>
<br>
Job Description for F&B or Food and Beverage Director<br>
JOB TITLE:  FOOD & BEVERAGE DIRECTOR / MANAGER<br>
REPORTS TO: General Manager<br>
 <br>
POSITION SUMMARY:<br>
 <br>
The Director of Food & Beverage is responsible for the daily operations of all phases of Food and Beverage Operations held in the Hotel; coordinate these activities on a daily basis; assist clients in program planning and menu selection.<br>
 <br>
Solicit local group Food & Beverage business; maintain the services and reputation of Your Hotel and act as a management representative to group clients.<br>
<br>
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:<br>
1.	Achievement of budgeted food sales, beverage sales, labor costs and profitability.<br>
2.	Completion of Customer Follow-up calls on a timely basis.<br>
3.	Timely analysis of Food & Beverage Prices in relation to competition.<br>
4.	Participation and input towards F&B Marketing activities.<br>
5.	Entertainment of potential and existing customers.<br>
6.	Preparation of Sales Promotions & Mailings.<br>
7.	Development and maintenance of all department control procedures.<br>
8.	Handle all Food & Beverage inquiries and ensure timely follow up on the same business day.<br>
9.	To co-ordinate with Sales and Catering Managers on all large group meeting/banquet planners their specific group requirements with the services & facilities offered. This includes proposals, contracts, estimated and actual function statements. With banquet or conferences, the Chef is to be included in food related discussions.<br>
10.	Maintenance of Hotel credit policies.<br>
11.	Completion of monthly forecast.<br>
12.	Attendance and participation at weekly F & B meeting and Department Head meeting.<br>
13.	To assist in menu planning and pricing.<br>
14.	Development and maintenance of department manual.<br>
15.	Supervision of weekly payroll input.<br>
16.	Be available to Hotel Staff at all times in case of emergency.<br>
17.	Must have a complete knowledge of Fire Procedures.<br>
18.	All other duties as directed by the General Manager.<br>
19.	Participation in Manager on Duty shifts as required.<br>
20.	Assure bar inventory for functions, including opening and closing inventories, accurate bar summaries and cash deposits are prepared.<br>
21.	Assure the maintenance of bar control policies.<br>
22.	Assure completion of requisitions where deemed necessary.<br>
23.	Assure the completion of weekly schedule and shift duties while A: maintaining a labor cost. B:. Assuring adequate and consistent levels of service.<br>
24.	Completion of monthly inventories.<br>
25.	Assure the ordering and purchasing of beer, wine, liquor, premix canisters and canned soft for Food& Beverage.<br>
26.	Purchasing of purchase requirements of small wares, linens requirements etc.<br>
27.	Consistent check of Banquet Food and Beverage quality, Banquet services and pallet presentation.<br>
28.	Ensuring that services meet customer specifications.<br>
29.	Liaise on an on-going basis with the Sales Department to ensure all client needs and requirements will be met.<br>
30.	Work with the Chef, Assistant of Food & Beverage and Catering Manager to ensure all arrangements and details are dealt with.<br>
31.	Establish a rapport with groups to ensure guest satisfaction and repeat business.<br>
32.	Minimize number of customer complaints.<br>
33.	Ensure a professional attitude and proper business attire when on property, ready to meet or service a client at any time.<br>
34.	Staff professional attitude and proper meeting Company appearance and uniform standards.<br>
35.	Teamwork-Relations with co-workers and management.<br>
36.	Quality of Food & Beverage services and department phone handling.<br>
37.	Responsible for staff training and development.<br>
38.	Ensure all staff have all required certification.<br>
39.	Personnel hiring and firing.<br>
40.	Proper hiring procedures followed, Proper termination procedures must be followed.<br>
41.	Department meeting being held monthly. High employee retention.<br>
42.	Personal development and growth.<br>
43.	Discipline of personnel when required.<br>
44.	Responsible for overseeing all scheduling within the department.<br>
45.	Participation towards overall Hotel Maintenance and cleanliness.<br>
46.	Achieving service that exceeds expectations.<br>
47.	Overall maintenance of the operation at a level in keeping with the standards prescribed.<br>
48.	Minimize the number of Workmen's Compensation claims.<br>
49.	Report any deficiencies in equipment and facilities.<br>
Education: Post Graduate or Degree or three years Diploma in hotel Management or equivalent work experience. <br>
 <br>
Experience: Previous experience in similar Job role or minimum Four years of work experience as Food and Beverage Manager or General Manager. Proven track records.<br>
<br>
Please reply to this ad with cover letter and resume and resumes are also being accepted at the Coast International Inn.<br>
3450 Aviation Ave.<br>
Anchorage, AK 99502  <br>
<br>
Salary based on experience.  Health benefits, 401K plan included.<br>
    </section>

